\ ?if : peek-if. Enters body when top is non-zero (truthy); branches over
\ body when top is zero. Value stays on the stack — not popped.

\ basic truthy / falsy
: maybe-yes ?if "yes" . then ;
3 maybe-yes drop cr               \ yes
0 maybe-yes drop cr               \ (nothing, just newline)

\ value preserved inside body — common use: act on the value conditionally
: doubled ?if 2 * then ;
3 doubled . cr                    \ 6
0 doubled . cr                    \ 0

\ ?if … else … then works (else uses the same slot mechanism)
: truthy ?if "truthy" . else "falsy" . then drop ;
1 truthy cr                       \ truthy
0 truthy cr                       \ falsy

\ peek semantics: body sees the original value still on top
: keeps ?if dup * then ;
4 keeps . cr                      \ 16
0 keeps . cr                      \ 0

\ empty stack underflow when executing body
: oops ?if 99 . then ;
oops
